BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Draft 2025 Consolidated Annual Performance Evaluation Report - Pub
 lic Comment Hearing
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T180000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T190000
UID:e32955f238ba52f02ac8ead28f2450bd@cityofevanston.org
DESCRIPTION:<p>Public comment Hearing for the Draft 2025 Consolidated Annu
 al Performance Evaluation Report (CAPER). The CAPER is part of the U.S. De
 partment of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) Consolidated Plan Process.
  This meeting will be an opportunity for the public to provide public comm
 ent on the Draft 2025 CAPER.&nbsp\;</p>\n<p><a href="https://us06web.zoom.
 us/j/89772617573?pwd=8C2cnH2CXpxrby5EZGvZHDL2xmUtXB.1" target="_blank">Joi
 n online via Zoom</a><br /><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAI
 pQLSe9rTC6H36PJYK4_ZvHEH8t8MI0oQ3E7K4VUIaRareJHnDtGw/viewform?usp=header" 
 target="_blank">Public Comment Sign up Form</a></p>\n<p><span style="font-
 weight: 400\;">The City of Evanston&rsquo\;s Draft 2025 Consolidated Annua
 l Performance and Evaluation Report (CAPER) discusses the City&rsquo\;s ac
 complishments during fiscal year 2025 in meeting its community development
  and housing goals using federal funds from the U.S. Department of Housing
  and Urban Development&rsquo\;s Community Development Block Grant (CDBG)\,
  HOME Investment Partnerships (HOME) and Emergency Solutions Grant (ESG) p
 rograms as stated in the 2025 Action Plan submitted to HUD.</span></p>\n<p
 ><span style="font-weight: 400\;">A draft of the 2025 Consolidated Annual 
 Performance and Evaluation Report (CAPER) may be viewed in person at the C
 ity of Evanston&rsquo\;s Clerk&rsquo\;s Office located at 909 Davis Street
 \, or online a</span><span style="font-weight: 400\;">t </span><a rel="noo
 pener" href="http://www.cityofevanston.org/conplan" target="_blank"><stron
 g>www.cityofevanston.org/conplan</strong></a><strong> </strong><span style
 ="font-weight: 400\;">through March 18\, 2026. </span></p>\n<p><span style
 ="font-weight: 400\;">The 15-day public comment period for the CAPER start
 ed on March 2\, 2026 and was initially scheduled to close on March 17\, 20
 26 at the Housing &amp\; Community Development Committee. To accommodate e
 lection day\, the public comment period has been extended and will instead
  close following any input received during the CAPER Public Comment Hearin
 g on Wednesday\, March 18\, 2026.<br /><br />For any questions\, contact h
 ousing@cityofevanston.org or 311.</span></p>
LOCATION:Lorraine Morton City Hall- Council Chamber (2nd floor\, 909 Davis
  St)
X-SOURCE:City of Evanston Meetings
END:VEVENT
